name: Dear Radical Self
description:
Digital Drawing

It's been awhile since the last time I want you away. I guess I will never able to go, I'm you after all. So bear with me, smoking our life away, after dinner in the mall entrance, just the two of us, the time passed by, as opposing the other way.

I know you're there, I can see. I don't want to ask the same question you don't want to answer. The existential talk, as you usually put it. Just seize the day, or carpe diem, ha, cliche am I right? Sweep the emotion in a motion.

So, please do, go on with your day, be yourself even none wants you. I will always got your back, my self.

Happy birthday and here is an early cringe birthday present in a very fast lane. Nothing's sort of Laura about it, but well, I'm politely asking and I’m sorry, are we decent?
